"In X-Men Destiny, players control the fate of one of three brand-new mutant characters forced to choose between saving humanity or ensuring its destruction. The branching storyline, penned by acclaimed Marvel writer Mike Carey, features a deep element of choice, allowing players to customize the path, powers and development of their character and to decide their role in the mutant cause alongside, or against, some of Marvel’s greatest X-Men franchise characters, such as Magneto, Cyclops, Wolverine and Gambit."

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hcs0b2KBudA&amp;feature=player_embedded
The latest trailer for <em>Legend of Zelda: Skyward Sword</em> features a love note, eyelash fluttering, and plenty of longing glances. It's nice to see that this time around we might actually get to see a convincing romance blossom between Link and Zelda. It's a promising concept that's never been fully realised in the series and I for one am happy to welcome it. Characterization has never been a strong suit for the series in spite of the amazingly expressive faces of the characters in <em>Wind Waker </em>and <em>Twilight Princess</em>. With the sheer amount of feeling you can get out of just watching this little trailer, you can tell Nintendo is aiming to give us more than pretty faces this time around. Although my personal opinion of the series has not been positive lately, this video put a smile on my face.

